<TITLE> Security heightened countrywide </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 22 (bdnews24.com)The government has ordered law enforcers countrywide to be on extra alert due to the Bangabandhu murder case proceedings and the recent bomb attack on Awami League MP Sheikh Fazle Noor Taposh, home minister Sahara Khatun said Thursday. Sahara told bdnews24.com on Thursday night, "The government was already conscious of security issues from the start of the case proceedings." "But law enforcing agencies, including RAB and police, have been given directions to be more alert." "Security has been tightened at all key points and installations in the capital and around the country," she said. Home secretary Abdus Sobhan Sikder also told bdnews24.com security at the prisons where the convicts in the Bangabandhu murder case are being held had been tightened. He said meetings headed by the home minister were held at the secretariat on Thursday with the heads of different law enforcing agencies. bdnews2
